cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

The paper deals with object classification and visual-semantic embedding, which are primarily topics in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed model involves learning discriminative visual features and semantic representations, which are also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of natural language descriptions for object classification, which falls under computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the experiments involve image datasets, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
